MUSORSTOM 4: Stn. CP153, “several well developed, flabellate colonies 30× 50 mm , stems basally polysiphonic; many appressed gonothecae […]. One large colony 30× 40 mm is holotype (MNHN-Hy. 1117)” (
Vervoort 1993
